1 orange
½ packet caster sugar
2 packet Cream Cheese
2 eggs
1 packet sour cream
1.5 packet cornflour
1 tsp cinnamon
1 packet Cherry Sauce

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Line the baking tin with two layers of baking paper then lightly brush
with oil.
• Zest orange, then cut in half. Measure 100g caster sugar.

• In a large bowl, place cream cheese and measured caster sugar. Using
electric beaters, beat until combined.
• Add the eggs and sour cream and beat with electric beaters to combine.
• Add cornflour, orange zest, the cinnamon and a pinch of salt. Mix well
to combine.
• Pour cheesecake mixture into the double lined baking tin.

• Bake for 30-40 minutes on the top rack of the oven until the cheesecake has
a little wobble in the centre.
• Allow to cool completely in the baking tin.
• Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine cherry sauce and a squeeze of
orange juice.

• Transfer cinnamon and orange baked cheesecake to a serving platter. Drizzle
over zesty cherry sauce.
• Slice and serve. Enjoy!